      "summary": "The song was released in 1993 as the second single from Björk's debut album, Debut. The song is about a boy who sees everything from a beauty point of view. The lyrics refer to a specific person, but Björk has refused to tell who he is. The music video features Björk rolling eggs across her face and upper body before she fries them. <a href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/Bj%C3%B6rk/_/Venus+as+a+Boy\">Read more on Last.fm</a>.",
